<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="reputation-n">reputation <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌrepju'teɪʃn/    美 /ˌrepju'teɪʃn/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>名声；名誉：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Typical of the Scotch, Burns <strong>had</strong> a <strong>reputation for</strong> being funny and charming.  
彭斯是个典型的苏格兰人，他以风趣和富有魅力而闻名。</p><footer>译林⑧ – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>earn / gain</strong> / acquire <strong>a good reputation as</strong> a doctor
作为医生获得好名声</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The doctor is skilled at treating heart trouble and never accepts any gift from his patients, so he has a very good <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (名声).  （2010 江苏改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. reputation  </p></div>